name: integer_u16_maximum
description: |
  This is the maximum u16 value, 65535, with every bit set. Adding 1 crosses the
  unsigned upper boundary and may trap, wrap to zero, saturate, or be widened
  before evaluation. Reinterpreting the same bytes as i16 produces -1, making it
  useful for detecting signedness mistakes in storage, comparison, and
  conversion code.
format: hex
decode-as: u16
pair:
  - with: one.input
    hint: tricky
tags:
  - "integer"
  - "unsigned-integer"
  - "u16"
  - "maximum"
  - "boundary"
  - "overflow"
  - "conversion"
  - "all-bits-set"
---
ff ff # 65535
